Put a #large saucepan{} of water with @salt{0.5%tsp} on to boil for the pasta. Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125}. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(peeled and sliced). Finely chop the @chives{1}(finely chopped).

> You can use scissors to chop the chives!

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #frying pan{} on high heat. Add the @chorizo{60g}(diced), stir-fry until just turning crispy, ~{2-3%mins}. Lower the heat to medium, stir in the tomatoes, onion and a little knob of @?butter{knob} (if you have some!) to the pan. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and give it all a good stir. Cover with a #lid{} (or foil) then leave to cook until the onions are soft and the tomatoes have burst, ~{10-12%mins}, stirring once or twice.

Meanwhile, add the @spaghetti{200%g} to the pan of boiling water and cook for ~{8%mins}. Once cooked, reserve some of the pasta water, then drain the pasta in a #colander{}, pop back in the pan, drizzle with a little @olive oil{drizzle} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

After 10-12 mins, remove the lid from the frying pan and stir in the garlic, @tomato puree{30g}, a small pinch of @chilli flakes{1%small pinch} (don't add all of them, you can add more later and they are spicy!) and the @red wine vinegar{12%ml}. Increase the heat slightly and bring to the boil. Cook for ~{30%seconds} then add the @reserved pasta water{150%ml} for the sauce.

Add the @diced chicken breast{260%g} into the sauce, mix together and cook for a further ~{9-11%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle. Taste and season with more salt and pepper if necessary. Add some more chilli flakes here if you want to!

Once the chicken is cooked, mix the drained spaghetti into the sauce and add a splash of @water{1%splash} if it looks a little dry! Toss everything together well then remove from the heat. Mix the chives into the pasta then divide between your #bowls{}.

> Buon Appetito!